      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">PO Strategy: Making the Most of the P Tile</h2>

      <p>P scores 3 points — above average for a consonant. PO lets you use it efficiently:</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Quick P dump:</span> With only 2 P-tiles in the bag, you might draw both. PO lets you shed one quickly while scoring 4 points — enough to stay competitive while improving your rack.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Premium square targeting:</span> P on a Double Letter scores 7 points for PO (6+1). P on a Triple Letter scores 10 points (9+1). Strong returns for a 2-tile play.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Crossword multiplier:</span> PO parallel to existing words creates multiple scoring words in one move. Each crossword formed scores independently, multiplying your total.</p>
        </div>
